06/06/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The country's economy has registered substantial progress in the past years, the IMF mission in Macedonia said Monday (5 June). During a meeting with Finance Minister Nikola Popovski and National Bank Governor Petar Gosev, IMF officials noted that in the past year, the country has brought inflation under control and managed to boost economic growth to 4 per cent. At the same time, the IMF experts called for more efforts in structural reform, as well as reform of the judiciary and the education system. They also highlighted the need to strengthen the capacity of the financial sector. (MIA - 05/06/06)
